dct_title_s: Kyongsong or Seoul (Keijo), Kyonggi-do (Keiki-do) Korea. A.M.S. L951
dct_description_sm: Alternate title: Kyonsong or Seoul (Keijo). In upper left margin: Korea city plans 1:12,500. Polyconic projection. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals and spot elevation. Depth shown by fathoms. Korean names transcribed according to the McCune-Reishauer system. Japanese forms of Korean names (shown in parentheses) transcribed according to the modified Hepburn (Romaji) system. On verso: "Administrative unit names". "3-46." Relief shown by contours, spot heights and hachures. Depths shown by soundings. Three classes of roads, three classes of railroads, and areas of vegetation and cultivation are shown. Administrative units and some buildings are named. "Korean names transcribed according to the McCune-Reischauer system, Japanese forms of Korean names (shown in parentheses) transcribed according to the modified Hepburn (Romaji) system." Military grid. Includes glossary of Korean, Japanese and English terms, inset map "Index to sources" and notes. AMS 1.
dct_publisher_sm: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1946.
